    <note>Cao(1) Guan [1667] Xiuli's [3875] son, Xiugu's [3874] nephew. Guan's younger brother, Jin(2) [21666], was given a salary on death of Xiugu, when he also became Xiugu's heir because the uncle was childless. Guan died in 1058. Since another brother of Xiugu, Xiumu [21663], had only one son, Di (not in dataset), and Jin died at age 25 when, as prefect of Fengzhou, he was killed when the Nong Zhigao rebels took the prefectural city, the family may have died out--Di also had only one son, Zhuan (not in dataset). XCB, 187.3b. CBD, 3, 2205.</note>
